  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment is accepted at MRL 2 despite explicitly low confidence (~50%) in hemolysis index predictions. The decision is grounded in the following structured evidence: (1) All 10 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required Gradation 2 levels; 3 factors are scoped out with documented justification. (2) The low confidence in HI predictions is honestly documented and traceable to two dominant sources: blood viscosity uncertainty (Sobol' S1=0.41) and yield stress uncertainty (S1=0.29), together accounting for 70% of output variance as established by the Sobol' sensitivity analysis. (3) The 95% prediction interval of ±34% on HI is wide but the central estimate (mean RH = 0.72) remains below the regulatory threshold of RH < 1 even at the upper bound (RH = 0.95 at 95th percentile), providing margin against the acceptance criterion. (4) Model influence is MEDIUM: physical bench testing confirms the direction of worst-case operating point identification, reducing reliance on the absolute accuracy of CFD HI predictions. (5) The sensitivity analysis (hasSensitivityAnalysis: true) documents that geometric tolerance inputs (clearance gap, rotational speed) have low Sobol' indices (S1 < 0.08), meaning the primary COU question — worst-case operating point identification — is robust to the dominant rheology uncertainties. (6) Discretization error is well-controlled (GCI 4.2%, ±5%) and contributes negligibly to total uncertainty. The team concludes that the residual uncertainty is acceptable for a Class II device at MRL 2 given the positive margin against the regulatory threshold, the honest documentation of all uncertainty sources, and the corroborating physical test evidence. No weakener conditions are present in this package.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
